{0 tempo-score}

`tempo-score` provides a Tempo-oriented musical representation:
- logical units (`start_unit`, `duration_units`) suitable for Tempo instants
- voices grouped by MIDI channel/bank/program
- transport metadata (meter, initial bpm, units per bar)
- timeline events for tempo changes and piano controls (CC64/66/67)
- a compact textual format (`tempo-score v2`, v1-compatible on read) for
  editing and exchange (`subdivision: 1/N`, no MIDI tick leak)
- a binary format (`tempo-score` binary v2, v1-compatible on read) for faster
  loading in applications (current writer emits v3; reader keeps v1/v2/v3
  compatibility)

Typical usage:
- import a MIDI file with {!Tempo_score.of_midi_file}
- optionally serialize with {!Tempo_score.to_text} or parse with {!Tempo_score.of_text}
- or serialize/load in binary with {!Tempo_score.to_binary}/{!Tempo_score.of_binary}
- schedule `note_on` / `note_off` in Tempo from unit indices
- keep Tempo as timeline owner (pause/restart/interactive control)
